  "body": "Extends the Phase 1 data foundation (PR #32) with the full Portfolio Manager pipeline: risk analytics, candidate scoring, LLM-driven holding review and investment decisions, and mock trade execution.\n\n## New modules\n\n### Pure Python analytics\n- **`portfolio/risk_evaluator.py`** — log returns, Sharpe, Sortino, VaR (≥20 obs guard), max drawdown, beta, sector concentration, portfolio-level aggregation, and `check_constraints()` (max positions / cash / position size / sector exposure)\n- **`portfolio/candidate_prioritizer.py`** — composite score: `conviction × thesis × diversification × held_penalty`; `prioritize_candidates()` with optional top-N\n\n### LLM agents (scanner pattern)\n- **`agents/portfolio/holding_reviewer.py`** — `create_holding_reviewer(llm)`, uses `run_tool_loop()` with `get_stock_data` + `get_news`; outputs `{ticker: {recommendation, confidence, rationale, key_risks}}` JSON for all open positions\n- **`agents/portfolio/pm_decision_agent.py`** — `create_pm_decision_agent(llm)`, pure-reasoning (no tools, macro_synthesis pattern); synthesizes risk metrics + holding reviews + ranked candidates into structured BUY/SELL/HOLD decision JSON\n\n### Trade execution (Phase 5)\n- **`portfolio/trade_executor.py`** — `TradeExecutor.execute_decisions()`: SELLs first, per-BUY pre-flight `check_constraints()`, graceful per-trade failure isolation, EOD snapshot via `PortfolioRepository`\n\n### Graph orchestration\n- **`portfolio/portfolio_states.py`** — `PortfolioManagerState(MessagesState)` with `Annotated[str, _last_value]` reducers on all mutable fields\n- **`graph/portfolio_setup.py`** + **`graph/portfolio_graph.py`** — `PortfolioGraph` mirroring `ScannerGraph`; sequential 6-node workflow:\n\n```\nSTART → load_portfolio → compute_risk → review_holdings\n      → prioritize_candidates → pm_decision → execute_trades → END\n```\n\nNon-LLM nodes receive `repo` and `config` via closure; LLM nodes (`review_holdings`, `pm_decision`) injected at construction time with mid/deep_think tiers.\n\n## Usage\n\n```python\nfrom tradingagents.graph.portfolio_graph import PortfolioGraph\n\ngraph = PortfolioGraph(config=my_config)\nresult = graph.run(\n    portfolio_id=\"uuid\",\n    date=\"2026-03-20\",\n    prices={\"AAPL\": 213.50, \"NVDA\": 875.00},\n    scan_summary=scanner_graph_output,  # from ScannerGraph.run()\n)\n# result[\"execution_result\"] — JSON with executed/failed trades and EOD snapshot\n# result[\"pm_decision\"]      — JSON with sells/buys/holds and portfolio thesis\n```\n\n## Also fixed\n- `tests/__init__.py` added — resolves `ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'tests.portfolio'` that broke `test_repository.py` collection\n- Debug streaming in `PortfolioGraph.run()` no longer invokes the graph twice when `debug=True`\n\n<!-- START COPILOT ORIGINAL PROMPT -->\n\n\n\n<details>\n\n<summary>Original prompt</summary>\n\nExtend the Portfolio Manager implementation by following and expanding upon the outlined development plan for Phase 1 through Phase 5. Implement the planned modules for risk evaluation, candidate prioritization, pipeline orchestration, decision-making, and trade execution.\n\nThe following is the prior conversation context from the user's chat exploration (may be truncated):\n\nUser: I would like you to read docs/agent /portfolio and PR#32 and continue implementation of portfolio manager according to the plan\n\nAssistant: To assist you with this request, I'll take the following steps:\n\n1. **Read the `docs/agent/portfolio` document** to understand the plan or specifications mentioned for the portfolio manager.\n2. **Examine the changes in Pull Request #32** to understand the updates and how they relate to the portfolio manager implementation.\n3. **Use both resources to guide the continuation of the portfolio manager's implementation.**\n\nLet me start by retrieving and analyzing the files and the PR.\n\nAssistant: The `docs/agent/portfolio` file retrieval failed, which limits my ability to reference design documentation stored there. However, I do know the details within Pull Request #32. This PR establishes a structured foundation for the portfolio manager data layer with fully-implemented `models.py` and `report_store.py`, as well as rigorous testing infrastructure. Here are the highlights:\n\n1. **`models.py` Enhancements**:\n    - Includes `to_dict()`, `from_dict()`, and `enrich()` methods for `Portfolio`, `Holding`, `Trade`, and `PortfolioSnapshot`.\n    - Explicit logic guards for zero-division and to ensure runtime-computed fields aren’t persisted in the database.\n\n2. **`report_store.py`**:\n    - Functions for handling JSON reports, structured error handling, and robust directory management for filesystem operations.\n\n3. **Database Updates**:\n    - SQL schema modifications to streamline constraints for `trades.action`.\n\n4. **Testing Infrastructure**:\n    - Comprehensive tests for core modules achieving over 90% coverage.\n\n5. **Goal & Structure**:\n   - Phase 1 focuses on introducing the entire data foundation, including creating portfolios, managing mock trades, and storing references on a filesystem.\n\nWould you like to proceed with extending what PR #32 laid out to further implement specifics of the Portfolio Manager? Let me know how you'd like this scoped. Or, should I retry accessing the project documentation file?\n\nUser: I would like you to extend the phase 1 and. Create a plan for the further development\n\nAssistant: Based on the work accomplished in Pull Request #32, here’s an extended implementation plan for Phase 1 and further future development towards completing the Portfolio Manager feature:\n\n---\n\n### **Phase 1 Completion Tasks**\n(Extend the data foundation and initial scaffolding)\n\n1. **Enhance Data Models (`models.py`):**\n   - Introduce optional fields for custom metadata (tags, notes).\n   - Add utility methods for JSON schema validation.\n   - Ensure support for multi-currency portfolios.\n\n2. **Reports (`report_store.py`):**\n   - Include support for versioned reports to enable historical insights.\n   - Add report types for:\n     - Risk Overview.\n     - Candidate Analysis Snapshot.\n\n3. **Database Schema Migration:**\n   - Improve schema versioning (`migrations/`) with change logs documented.\n   - Create separate data partitions or columns designed to handle derived statistics.\n\n4. **Tests:**\n   - Consolidate feature edge cases and integrate benchmark datasets.\n   - Automate mock Supabase tests for cloud deployments.\n\n5. **Environment Configurations:**\n   - Improve integration with environment variables (`config.py`) by adding runtime dynamic configurations.\n   - Generation of user-facing config templates.\n\n---\n\n### **Phase 2: Candidate Recommendation Pipeline**\n1. **Signal Evaluation and Inputs:**\n   - Build the `Holding` risk evaluator interface (read 7-day price history).\n   - Integrate API adapters for macro signals e.g. volatility, sentiment.\n\n2. **Analytics Pipeline:**\n   - Construct underlying methods for Sharpe, Beta pre-filter `evaluate()`.\n   - Prototype loops integrate Holding weight auto-balances dummy logic output numbers.\n\nILogger ML concierge BACK \"</BACK future seamlesslysecurity\"\n\nUser: Yes continue as you planned\n\nUser: Can you finish you plan it seems it is interrupted\n\nAssistant: Apologies for the interruption earlier. I will now complete the extended development plan for the Portfolio Manager based on the foundation laid in Phase 1.\n\n---\n\n### **Phase 2: Candidate Recommendation Pipeline (Continued)**\n3. **Pipeline Orchestration:**\n   - Develop `ScannerGraph` to identify market opportunities as JSON data.\n   - Implement the `evaluate_candidates()` function to run analytics workflows per ticker.\n   - Optimize workflows to utilize multiprocessing for concurrent analysis.\n\n4. **Risk Evaluation Module:**\n   - Introduce risk metrics for candidates and existing holdings:\n     - VaR (5% perc...\n\n</details>\n\n\n\n<!-- START COPILOT CODING AGENT SUFFIX -->\n\n*This pull request was created from Copilot chat.*\n>\n\n<!-- START COPILOT CODING AGENT TIPS -->\n---\n\n📍 Connect Copilot coding agent with [Jira](https://gh.io/cca-jira-docs), [Azure Boards](https://gh.io/cca-azure-boards-docs) or [Linear](https://gh.io/cca-linear-docs) to delegate work to Copilot in one click without leaving your project management tool.",
